03/07/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The war crimes court on Thursday (July 2nd) sentenced former Serb police officer Damir Ivankovic to 14 years in prison in connection with the murders of over 200 Muslims and Croats in August 1992. 
Ivankovic, 39, admitted involvement in the murders on Vlasic Mountain in central BiH. 
(AFP, Nezavisne Novine BTA - 02/07/09)
